snippet.title: Rs 500, Rs 1000 Note Ban: The Surgical Strike To Fight Corruption

localized.description:
Rs 500, Rs 1000 Note Ban: The Surgical Strike To Fight Corruption.
PM Narendra Modi announces that currency notes of Rs 1000 and Rs 500 will not be legal tender from November 10 midnight. Modi government takes such bold step to curb black money, corruption and fake currency and terrorism. Common peoples are unable to withdraw Rs 50 and Rs 100 notes as all banks and ATMs are closed today.
People can exchange or submit 500 rupee and 1000 rupee notes in the banks and post offices. Soon government will launch new currency notes of 500 and 2000.
